title: [Temple Burrow, Cholen Lane]
description: A small group of blue-robed monks walks through this area, heading north up a path in the glacier.  Thick-walled houses face the glacier, sweet smelling wood smoke pluming from their chimneys.
A temple guard walks, bending his cowled head into the wind, north up a path in the glacier.  Thick-walled houses face the glacier, earthy smoke from peat fires pluming from their chimneys.
paths: Obvious paths: north, east, south, southwest
